{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"v08egsqxbv3m0u532jzo03l","title":"Specify alternate project-level README on Github","desc":"","updated":1646400894358,"created":1646400876711,"custom":{},"fname":"Specify alternate project-level README on Github","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"0ead93e6cc3090616a987a50d91f4b33","links":[{"from":{"fname":"root","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":3,"offset":2},"end":{"line":1,"column":55,"offset":54},"indent":[]},"value":"Specify alternate project-level README on Github","alias":"Specify alternate project-level README on Github"}],"anchors":{"on-linux-and-mac":{"type":"header","text":"On Linux and Mac","value":"on-linux-and-mac","line":17,"column":0,"depth":3},"on-windows":{"type":"header","text":"On Windows","value":"on-windows","line":24,"column":0,"depth":3}},"children":[],"parent":"1a4tk6w6d1hqa9hydfatd2h","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"specify-alternate-project-level-readme-on-github\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#specify-alternate-project-level-readme-on-github\"></a>Specify alternate project-level README on Github</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/49981731/5930856\">Stackoverflow source</a>\n<br>\n<br></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-readmes\">Github Searches for README.md in a few places</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If you put your README file in your repository's root, docs, or hidden .github directory, GitHub will recognize and automatically surface your README to repository visitors.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>To use another file as the project level readme create a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Symbolic_link\">Symlink</a> from the file to a location inside <code>.github</code> folder <strong>in the project root</strong>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"on-linux-and-mac\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#on-linux-and-mac\"></a>On Linux and Mac</h3>\n<pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-Shell\"><span class=\"token comment\"># From repository root</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">mkdir</span> .github\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">cd</span> .github\n<span class=\"token function\">ln</span> -s <span class=\"token punctuation\">..</span>/docs/projectname/some-README.md README.md  \n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"on-windows\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#on-windows\"></a>On Windows</h3>\n<p>Symbolic links are only available on NTFS filesystems on Windows Vista or later, and creating them requires <a href=\"https://blogs.windows.com/windowsdeveloper/2016/12/02/symlinks-windows-10/\">Developer Mode</a>. They are not supported by <a href=\"https://github.com/git-for-windows/git/wiki/Symbolic-Links\">Git on Windows out of the box</a>.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><code>cd</code> to the root of the repo and enable symlinks:\n<pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-Shell\">  <span class=\"token function\">git</span> config core.symlinks <span class=\"token boolean\">true</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n<li>Launch <code>cmd.exe</code> as Administrator:\n<pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-Shell\"><span class=\"token comment\"># From repository root</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">mkdir</span> .github\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">cd</span> .github\nmklink README.md <span class=\"token punctuation\">..</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>docs<span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>projectname<span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>some-README.md\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n<li>Ensure there are no other README files anywhere else that github searches in.</li>\n<li>Windows users who clone the repository won't get a symlink automatically. If they wish to have that behaviour they should clone with a special argument:\n<pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-Shell\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> clone -c core.symlinks<span class=\"token operator\">=</span>true <span class=\"token operator\">&#x3C;</span>repo-url<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/\">Root</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"1a4tk6w6d1hqa9hydfatd2h","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":1652154211505,"created":1646400719607,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"5dc089f99d65a055df3527c66e9f3ccb","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"1a4tk6w6d1hqa9hydfatd2h","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"Specify alternate project-level README on Github","alias":"Specify alternate project-level README on Github","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":3,"offset":2},"end":{"line":1,"column":55,"offset":54},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"Specify alternate project-level README on Github"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"1a4tk6w6d1hqa9hydfatd2h","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"Calculate Intercept of a Linearly moving body","alias":"Calculate Intercept of a Linearly moving body","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":10,"offset":231},"end":{"line":5,"column":59,"offset":280},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"Calculate Intercept of a Linearly moving body"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"1a4tk6w6d1hqa9hydfatd2h","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"Links","alias":"Links","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":5,"offset":286},"end":{"line":7,"column":14,"offset":295},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"Links"}}],"anchors":{"todo":{"type":"header","text":"TODO","value":"todo","line":9,"column":0,"depth":3},"links":{"type":"header","text":"Links","value":"links","line":13,"column":0,"depth":3}},"children":["dzr6esc9es3dm2na3pv8hh1","v08egsqxbv3m0u532jzo03l"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"- [[Spe